      "raw_text": "A suit for $50,500 due on a writ\nten order for land scrip was brought\nyesterday by the w. E. Moses Land\nCo. against the Stacks-Gibbs Lum-\nDer Co. in the federal court. The\nlumber company wanted 10000\nacres Of Northern Pacific land in\nIdaho and offered to pay $50,500 for\nit. The land company secured the\nscrip but the lumber company re-\nfused to take 1t."
